## Requires ##
* https://github.com/Jordach/comfy-plasma - Plasma Noise for ComfyUI
  - Plasma Noise Generator
* https://github.com/DeInfernal/StupidSimpleNodes - Stupid Simple Nodes
  - Seed Nodes
  - Addition nodes
  - INT nodes
  - FLOAT nodes
  - Sampler/Scheduler nodes
* https://github.com/BlenderNeko/ComfyUI_ADV_CLIP_emb - Advanced CLIP Text Encode
  - Clip Prompts (Advanced) -> merged with Prompt Control
* https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI_experiments/blob/master/sampler_rescalecfg.py - Rescale CFG
* https://github.com/asagi4/comfyui-prompt-control - Prompt Control
  - Prompt to Schedule
  - Schedule to Conditioning
* Probably, 8 GB VRAM

nodes.title: About
widgets_values:
# Interfacial Workflow / Made by Project Soulstealer #

Interface: Variational Detail Enhancer
Version: v1.1.0

Detailer is pretty much the same as Generator, but it makes better detailing on the image. To use it, copy all settings from your prompt/query and *enlarged* image (you can use Upscaler for that). It makes 16 variations of image, allowing you to mix and match certain details with Photoshop manually, or simply select best variant here. Comes with much better prompt addon.

0-3 indicates shifted seed (is a different variants of image)
I-IV indicates shifted denoise value (how close will be to initial image, bigger the number closer to original)

Color Coding:
Cyan = Input nodes. You set information about what you want to those.
Yellow = Processing nodes. Don't touch those.
Green = Output nodes. This is where you get your result.
Black = Debug/Processing nodes. This is where you can see intermediate results.
